  <body>
    <main>
        <div class="form-content">
            <h1>2</h1>
            <h3>matching group numbers to what it does<br>---</h3>
            <!--
            struct FormWiz1 {
                pub site_url: String,
                pub item_regex: String,
            }
            -->
            <form action="/generate-3" method="post">
                <div class="form-item-readonly">
                    <label for="site_url">site url</label>
                    <input type="text" name="site_url" value="{{site_url}}" readonly/>
                </div>

                <div class="form-item-readonly">
                    <label for="items_regex">item filter</label>
                    <textarea type="input" id="items_regex" name="items_regex" readonly>{{items_regex}}</textarea>
                </div>

                <div class="form-item">
                  <p>
                  Since the groups are just numbered in order from first to last, step 2 requires you to match the groups found in step 1 using your pattern (the groups are where
                  you placed the selectors {%}). You need to input the number of the group for the respective fields.
                  See the <a href="#example-section">example below</a>.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div class="form-item">
                <label>here are the example groups from the first match found while using your pattern:</label>
                <div class="group-box">
                {{#each items_preview}}
                <p>
                  group {{this.[0]}}: {{this.[1]}}
                </p>
                {{/each}}
                </div>
                </div>

                <div class="form-item">
                <label for="item_title_no">group number for item title*</label>
                <input required type="number" id="item_title_no" name="item_title_no" min="1" max="3">
                </div>

                <div class="form-item">
                <label for="item_url_no">group number for item url</label>
                <input type="number" id="item_url_no" name="item_url_no" min="1" max="3">
                </div>

                <div class="form-item">
                <label for="item_content_no">group number for item content</label>
                <input type="number" id="item_content_no" name="item_content_no" min="1" max="3">
                </div>

                <button type="submit">Next</button>

                <div class="form-item">
                <h3 id="example-section">example</h3>
                <div class="form-item">
                <label>say your pattern matched the following groups:</label>
                <div class="group-box">
                  <p>
                    group 1: https://plurrrr.com/archive/2023/07/07.html#nix-shell-template
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    group 2: Nix shell template
                  </p>
                </div>
                </div>
                <p>
                  In this example, group 1 is the url of the article you want to extract. This happened
                  because the url literally came before anything else in the raw site source code. Thus, you
                  would put 1 as the entry in <a href="#item_url_no">group number for item url</a>.
                </p>
                <p>
                  Similarly, group 2 would be the title that you want to extract and so you would put a 2
                  as the entry in <a href="#title_url_no">group number for item url</a>. The title is the only
                  required field so you are able to keep everything else blank if it isn't needed.
                </p>
                </div>
            </form>
        </div>
